<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The assertion compares two local variables that, by construction in the preceding code, will always be equal: new_used_size is computed as used_size + pos->header_size + pos->value_size + 4, and the code then increments used_size by exactly those same amounts before reaching the assertion. The mhd_assert call has no observable side effects in this context, so its execution does not alter program behaviour; removing it would not change the program’s behaviour. Therefore this assertion is dead code and violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 2.2.
</scenario>

